{
  "local_port": 59992,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I create hotspot for windows 10?",
  "response": "Creating a hotspot in Windows 10 allows you to share your internet connection with other devices, such as smartphones, tablets, or other computers. Here's how you can set it up:\n\n### **Method 1: Using Windows Settings**\n1. **Open Settings**:\n   - Press `Windows + I` to open the Windows Settings.\n   \n2. **Go to Network & Internet**:\n   - Click on **Network & Internet**.\n\n3. **Select Mobile Hotspot**:\n   - In the left-hand menu, click on **Mobile Hotspot**.\n\n4. **Configure the Hotspot**:\n   - Under **Share my Internet connection from**, select the network connection you want to share (e.g., Wi-Fi or Ethernet).\n   - Click **Edit** to set a Network name (SSID) and Network password.\n\n5. **Turn on the Hotspot**:\n   - Toggle the **Share my Internet connection with other devices** switch to **On**.\n\n6. **Connect Other Devices**:\n   - On your other devices, search for the new Wi-Fi network (the SSID you set) and connect using the password you configured.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 2: Using Command Prompt**\n1. **Open Command Prompt as Administrator**:\n   - Press `Windows + X` and select **Command Prompt (Admin)** or **Windows Terminal (Admin)**.\n\n  > **Note**: If you see PowerShell instead of Command Prompt, you can use PowerShell for this process.\n\n2. **Create the Hotspot**:\n   - Run the following command to set up the hotspot:\n     ```\n     netsh wlan set hostednetwork mode=allow ssid=YourNetworkName key=YourPassword\n     ```\n     Replace `YourNetworkName` with the desired network name and `YourPassword` with your chosen password.\n\n3. **Start the Hotspot**:\n   - Run the following command to start the hotspot:\n     ```\n     netsh wlan start hostednetwork\n     ```\n\n4. **Share Your Internet Connection**:\n   - Open **Control Panel** > **Network and Sharing Center** > **Change adapter settings**.\n   - Right-click the active internet connection (e.g., Wi-Fi or Ethernet) and select **Properties**.\n   - Go to the **Sharing** tab, check **Allow other network users to connect through this computer's Internet connection**, and select the hosted network connection (e.g., \"Local Area Connection*\").\n\n5. **Connect Other Devices**:\n   - Search for the new Wi-Fi network on your other devices and connect using the password you set.\n\n---\n\n### **Stop the Hotspot**\n- To stop the hotspot, use the following command in Command Prompt:\n  ```\n  netsh wlan stop hostednetwork\n  ```\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
